Petrol prices have fallen to their lowest level in three years, new figures have revealed.

The drop means a family with two cars is paying roughly £11.90 less a month on fuel for each vehicle.

Prices have been driven down because of falling decline from countries such as China.

But motoring campaigners have warned the costs could soon rise dramatically because of Russia’s annexation of the Crimea.

